      • RATE_INITIALIZATION_FINISHED

        public static final SystemAlert.Alerts RATE_INITIALIZATION_FINISHED
        When a rate initialization is finished, this alert is fired. It means the system can be put online again. Arguments: 0: the currency name; 1: a string indicating what type of rates (A, D, I).

      • RATE_INITIALIZATION_STARTED

        public static final SystemAlert.Alerts RATE_INITIALIZATION_STARTED
        A Rate initialization has started. The system has been set offline, and cannot be set online until it is finished. Arguments: 0: the currency name; 1: a string indicating what type of rates (A, D, I).

      • RATE_INITIALIZATION_FAILED

        public static final SystemAlert.Alerts RATE_INITIALIZATION_FAILED
        A Rate initialization has failed due to some encountered exception. Arguments: 0: the currency name; 1: the id of the last correctly processed transaction.
